      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, if it\u0027s passed to the kernel directly, then it\u0027s probably OK due to the copy_from_user() to a properly-aligned buffer.\n\nFor the thing I was looking at (building policies into the crosvm binary, https://crbug.com/1052126), we would want to pass the compiled bpf along to minijail so that it can do all of its normal setup stuff.  libminijail.rs\u0027s parse_seccomp_program() is almost what we want, except that reads the bpf from a file rather than accepting a buffer. That function has the alignment checks I ran into, and it seems justified, since it\u0027s passing the buffer to minijail_set_seccomp_filters(), which accesses the buffer through a `struct sock_filter *` inside `struct sock_fprog`.",
